<TABLE WIDTH=95%><TR><TD><B><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bquelliousquarters><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Quellious Quarters</FONT></A></B><BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/fquelliousquartersgeneral><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>General</FONT></A></B><BR><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<B>> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Re: I refuse to be denied</FONT></B></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/fquelliousquartersgeneral.showAddTopicScreenFromWeb><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/newTopic1.gif border=0></A>&nbsp; </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/fquelliousquartersgeneral.showMessage?topicID=1810.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/fquelliousquartersgeneral.showMessage?topicID=1834.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><TR><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#000000><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#778899>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top BGCOLOR=#000000><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#778899>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utamas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tamas</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Orc Runner</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#00ffff>9/27/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#00ffff>11:25:22 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.quellious.net/images/tamasicon.gif   WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B>&nbsp<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: I refuse to be denied</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I've sat back and observed these debates, I've locked nothing, edited nothing, said nothing, but I speak up now. <br>
<br>
Here's my take on the issues. <br>
<br>
Someone poached GE's Vox spawn. That was wrong, but I fail to see how that makes this website and its staff the villains. None of us participated in the aforementioned poaching in any way. All we did was a moderator removed a post that was deemed to be inflammatory, as per this site's policy. I have no chronological order, many of these posts were deleted before I ever saw them (I take a day away from the boards and all hell breaks loose, as usual). Some threads got removed and all sorts of people started clamoring and demanding policy clarifications. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Edit: I have since seen the deleted threads, and personally, I agree that they weren't in need of deletion, and were in fact just moved, but there's not much point to putting them back now, is there?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
When the planes/dragon scheduling was being debated, the staff of this website were called fascists, dictators, and worse when all they were trying to do was stop total chaos and provide a framework so everyone has access to these raids. Now that someone has chosen to violate that system, people make it like it's QQ's fault? We repeatedly stated up front that we were providing a forum to schedule raids, and had no ability or authority to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  enforce</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> said schedules. So now we get called &quot;spineless&quot; for not enforcing them. Damned if we do, damned if we don't. So, the affected guilds have come to terms now, but we at QQ are the villains? And get this. The affected guilds came to terms, privately, via other messageboards and email, for the most part. Yes, they were able to discuss the issues without putting them here.<br>
<br>
Some posts were deleted, and maybe not for the most logical of reasons. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Deal with it.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> They're gone, adios, bye-bye, in post heaven (or hell), poof, history, they ain't comin back. If I haven't made myself clear, a deleted post is irretrievable.<br>
<br>
Now, the constructive thing to come from all this is that we at QQ have devised a new policy. Posts are no longer immediately (and thus permanently) deleted. Instead, they get moved into a private forum where the other moderators can take a look and make a group decision what to do. Sure, that might take time, none of us are available 24/7. As evidenced by the fact that some posts were deleted, some people have different perspectives as to what's hot stuff, and this has led to questions of why was this moderated but that wasn't? Hopefully, as a result of this, the policy of this board can be applied somewhat more uniformly when decisions are made by multiple moderators rather than just one.<br>
<br>
I'm going to say this for the umpteenth time. We do this as a public service, of our own freewill, for no compensation. Pantera spends about 5 times as much time maintaining this site as she does playing EQ anymore, and all many people can do is bitch that the site's not perfect. Nobody thinks of how she has sacrificed her own play time out of a love for the game and desire to provide this website to the community. Before you criticize, I suggest you ask yourself: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Could I create a better website? Am I willing to take crap from everyone about everything? Am I willing to virtually stop playing EQ to provide a forum for other EQ players to use?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> If you answered no to even one of these questions, I say to you, put a cork in it, you have no right to criticize anyone. You can offer feedback and suggestions that you think might improve the site, but you have zero right to cast aspersions upon those who are willing to take on the thankless task that running this site has become.<br>
<br>
And to those who talk about making a site to compete with this one, I say <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  GO FOR IT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> because once you get it up and running, and if it does succeed, you'll see how it feels to be in our shoes.</font><P>Tamas Sturmpanzer <BR>
A Kinder, Gentler Smartass<BR>
Dragon's Bane Guild Officer<BR>
Quellious Quarters staff <BR>
